<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-474-525  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 474 525.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 10 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software Japan opens Windows 3.0 in Japan. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Japan (distribution).andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Computer industryMarket EntrySoftware packagesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SOFTWARE JAPAN OPENS WINDOWS 3.0 IN JAPAN TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 SEP 10 (NB) --Major personal computer distributor Software Japan will import from the U.S.andO;application software written for MS Windows 3.0 and will encourage sales andsupport of the software among Japanese software vendors.andM;Windows 3.0 has several enhancements over its earlier incarnation, such as animproved graphic user interface (GUI), expandable memory without an EMS(Extended Memory Specification) board, and enhanced network connectivity.andO;There are now 150 different applications which run under Windows 3.0 on theU.S.andP;  market.andM;Software Japan will initially distribute 30 of them, including wordprocessors, databases, utilities, and networking applications.andP;  A rewrite tothe Japanese language will be conducted by third parties in the U.S.andP;  throughSoftware Japan's partner, Pacific Enterprise, in California.andP;  Japanesesoftware houses, which will receive the software from Software Japan, willnot be involved with technical matters but will simply conduct sales andsupport duties in Japan.andM;Software Japan hopes its distribution of Windows 3.0 applications will speedup Japan's shift to networking environments, in which Windows are auser-friendly interface.andM;Having already wrapped up sales negotiations with U.S.andP;  software houses,Software Japan will release the applications by the time the Japanese versionof Windows 3.0 is introduced in Japan.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19900906)</TEXT></DOC>